But as they fled on stolen motorbikes, a motor scooter and a BMW car, the rider of the scooter Connor Groake lost control and both he and Sam Curtin, who was still wearing his burka, were tackled to the ground by passers-by. 

The gang, armed with axes and other equipment, had also worn burkas to raid a jewellery store in Windsor two months earlier.

During the 'well-planned robbery' at Robert Gatward jewellers in King Edward Court the gang smashed display cabinets stealing 19 Rolex watches costing between £3,000 and £31,650 each.

As they ran through the pedestrian zone, one of the burqa clad men wielded an axe raised above his head to 'ward off anyone who may have sought to impede their escape.'

